description._content: Original Collection: Harriet's Collection Item Number: HC0596 Image Description: This building was erected in 1907 as the Benton County National Bank, and became the Benton County State Bank in 1916. The basement featured a barbershop and Turkish baths. A street light hangs over the intersection of 2nd and Madison. You can find this image by searching for the item number by clicking here.
